                  display_name:
                    "What all inputs are taken into consideration on the hair test?",
                  faq_ans:
                    "Hairloss is as much internal as it is external. Understanding why it is happening is key to solving the issue. The Traya Hair Test is a comprehensive analysis that considers a range of critical inputs that help us know the root cause of your hairloss and accordingly create your personalised hair regrowth plan. Here's a glimpse into the key factors we take into consideration:\n\nAge:  Hair follicles weaken and slow down as you get older. The connection between age and your hair lies in the gradual weakening of your hair follicles over time, which can lead to hair loss. The regenerative capacity also decreases with age. Understanding your age helps set realistic expectations for your hair regrowth journey.\n\nHair Loss Stage:  Hair loss is not a one-size-fits-all problem. Your hair can be in different stages, and each stage demands a specific approach. Understanding your hair loss stage is like having a guideline; the right treatment at the right stage can make a significant difference in your regrowth journey.\n\nLifestyle:  Your daily habits play a crucial role in your hair health. Your diet provides vital nutrients necessary for hair growth, such as vitamins and minerals. The concept of 'Pitta Dosha' from Ayurveda relates to dietary imbalances that can adversely affect hair health. Exercise enhances blood flow to the hair follicles, promoting growth and reducing stress, a known factor in hair loss. Quality sleep is critical as it allows your body to repair and regenerate hair follicles. Stress can trigger a condition called Telogen Effluvium, disrupting the hair growth cycle by prematurely pushing hair follicles into the resting phase. This results in a noticeable shedding of hair a few months later. Understanding the 'why' and 'how' of these connections is essential in understanding the root causes of your hair loss.\n\nMedical History:  Some medical conditions, including thyroid problems, diabetes, heart issues, and certain medications, have the potential to disrupt your hair's growth cycle. By delving into your medical history, we can precisely pinpoint how these factors impact your hair health. For example, thyroid issues can lead to hormonal imbalances, while diabetes can affect blood circulation to the scalp. In females, even pregnancy and menopause periods induce hairfall. During pregnancy, elevated oestrogen levels can result in healthier hair, but postpartum hormonal shifts often trigger considerable hair shedding. Menopause involves declining oestrogen levels, leading to hair thinning. Recognizing these connections is vital in ensuring that your hair regrowth plan is not only effective but also safe.\n\nGut Health:  Your gut is the gatekeeper to your hair's potential. It plays an essential role in nutrient absorption, ensuring that your body receives the essential vitamins and minerals necessary for healthy hair.\n\nEnergy Levels:  Low energy levels is because of weakened metabolism, where your food does not get absorbed properly and thus the required nutrients don't reach your organs. Low energy levels can be a symptom of underlying health issues like anaemia, chronic stress, and a weakened immune system, all of which can contribute to hair loss. Recognizing low energy as a possible indicator of these issues is vital.\n\nScalp Picture: As part of the diagnostic process, we ask you to provide a snapshot of your scalp's health. The scalp picture helps our doctors in prescribing the right medication dosage before we ship your kit. It is also used by our Hair coaches when they speak with you, and helps them track your progress.\n\nIn conclusion, the Traya Hair Test is an in-depth and holistic approach to understanding the root causes of your hairloss. It goes beyond surface-level solutions by examining various internal factors that contribute to hair health. This comprehensive analysis helps us customise a personalised hair regrowth plan that addresses your unique needs and conditions. It's not just a test; it's your journey to a healthier and happier you.\n",
