                  faq_ans:
                    "1. Eligibility Criteria \n\nIn order to become eligible to claim  refund under this Money Back Policy, , you need to mandatorily fulfill the following requirements: \nYou must have used the complete plan as recommended to you post completion of the hair test on the Platform and have followed all the guidelines, plans, instructions as may be communicated by us to you from time to time.\nReligiously followed the treatment and purchased the complete kits for 5 consecutive months within a period of 6 months (Order number and date of purchases will be used to verify eligibility for the refund).\nYou should have shared/uploaded your scalp images every month since the beginning of the treatment on the Platform.\nIf the results as specified below in the table have not been achieved post the completion of the treatment (i.e. post the expiration of 5 months or 8 months, whichever is applicable based on your treatment plan).\nRefund to be raised within 30 days after the 5th-month or 8th-month order \n\n2. It is hereby clarified that a user will become eligible to claim a refund under this Money Back Policy ONLY if all the conditions specified above are met and fulfilled. \n\n3. Exceptions:\n\nAdditionally, you will not be eligible to claim refund under this Money Back Policy if you are suffering or have suffered with any of these pre-existing health conditions listed below or in the event you are diagnosed with these health conditions during the course of the treatment:\n\na.  Hashimoto's thyroiditis \nb.  Alopecia Areata \nc.  Folliculitis\nd.  Psoriasis and eczema \ne.  Cancer patients \nf.   Previously undergone transplant \ng.  Tinea capitis\nh.  Trichotillomania\ni.    Lichen plano pilaris (LPP)\nj.    Fungal scalp infection (Ex: Kerion and Favus)\nk.   Scarring alopecia ",
